5000|$|Bayrou {{was married}} in 1971 to Élisabeth <b>Perlant</b> {{also known as}} [...] "Babette". He and <b>Perlant</b> have six {{children}}, Hélène, Marie, Dominique, Calixte and Agnes. The children were raised on the farm where Bayrou was born and Bayrou currently lives there with <b>Perlant.</b>|$|E
50|$|Jean-Baptiste <b>Perlant</b> (born 22 February 1977) is {{a former}} {{professional}} tennis player from France.|$|E
50|$|His most {{noteworthy}} performance {{came in the}} 1998 French Open, {{the only}} Grand Slam of his career. The Spaniard had a five set opening round win over Jean-Baptiste <b>Perlant.</b> He then lost in straight sets to eventual champion Carlos Moyá, but would come close to winning the second set tiebreak, which lasted for 30 points.|$|E
50|$|<b>Perlant</b> {{made his}} Grand Slam {{debut in the}} 1998 French Open. He lost his opening match to Spaniard Jose Imaz-Ruiz in five sets. At the US Open later that year, he {{defeated}} world number 38 Jason Stoltenberg, who had previously reached the semi-finals of Wimbledon. In the second round he met seventh seed Alex Corretja and again lost a five set match.|$|E

